#Text=Fort Pierce
#Text=Fort Pierce is a small city on the Treasure Coast of Florida .
#Text=The city is most commonly referred to as " The Fort " in reference to the old fort on Indian River Drive .
#Text=Understand

#Text=Fort Pierce is the oldest incorporated city in St. Lucie County , with a bustling and historic downtown area , close location to beaches on the Indian River Lagoon and the Atlantic Ocean by its extension to Hutchinson Island , and many famous celebrities visiting every summer at the Sunrise Theatre .

#Text=Ft. Pierce has a population of 43,601 by the 2013 US Census Estimate ; Fort Pierce is also a part of the Port St. Lucie metropolitan area , or the Treasure Coast , an area populated at almost 600,000 .

#Text=Fort Pierce is a small railroad city along Florida 's east coast , being the location of a mid-sized rail yard with track rights owned by the Florida East Coast Railroad , with track all the way to Miami and Jacksonville , and South Central Florida Express , with track from the downtown yard to Clewiston and Sebring .
#Text=FP is becoming more and more modernized , but slowly and steadily .

#Text=Downtown is considered the hot-spot of the city due to its blossoming commercialism , amazing Spanish-colonial buildings , celebrities performing at the Sunrise Theatre , and an amazing Christmas display yearly at Avenues A and Orange .
#Text=There 's a lot of fun going on with the marina and many interesting shops on the thoroughfares of Orange Avenue and Avenue D.
#Text=By car
#Text=Fort Pierce , like many cities has many major highways running through the city .
#Text=Major highways include I-95 , US-1 , and Florida 's Turnpike .
#Text=By Interstate 95 , you can access Fort Pierce by :
#Text=Exit 126 at Midway Road .
#Text=Going west will take you to Okeechobee Road , which is what the locals call State Road 70 .
#Text=Going east will take you to the beach .
#Text=Exit 129 at Okeechobee Road .
#Text=There are many hotels and fast food restaurants near by .
#Text=Going west will take you to Okeechobee and further to Bradenton .
#Text=Going east will put you closer into the heart of downtown .
#Text=Exit 131 at Orange Avenue .
#Text=Going west will take you out to the " country " area of the city with many ranches .
#Text=Going east will take you into downtown .
#Text=Exit 138 at Indrio Road .
#Text=Services are east of the exit .
#Text=By Florida 's Turnpike , you can access Fort Pierce by :
#Text=Exit 152 at SR 70 , or Okeechobee Road .
#Text=One special thing about the Okeechobee Road area between I-95 and the Turnpike is that it is considered to be a crossroads , where two highways are within a driving range of less than a mile .
#Text=Businesses , from hotels to restaurants , are abundant in this State Road 70 corridor .
#Text=Businesses along State Road 70 do n't just exist at the cross roads , but also run along to US-1 .
#Text=US-1 and A1A run through the heart of downtown , and A1A almost parallels US-1 .
#Text=A1A runs along the barrier islands of the east coast , from Miami to the Jacksonville area .
#Text=The local name for A1A on Hutchinson Island South crossing onto US-1 is " Seaway Drive " .
#Text=By plane
#Text=Fort Pierce is home to the St. Lucie County International , the local airport .
#Text=Here , you can buy a plane to fly from place to place , due to no commercial flights .
#Text=St. Lucie County International Airport , 3000 Curtis King Blvd. , ☏ +1 772-462-1732 .
#Text=The only airport serving the county .
#Text=No commercial service yet , so bring your own plane .
#Text=If you want to get in by a commercial flight , your best options are :
#Text=Orlando International Airport , 1 Jeff Fuqua Boulevard , Orlando , FL 32827 , ☏ +1 407-825-2001 .
#Text=This airport is outside of the region , but is used to get into the region , serving almost all global US cities .
#Text=Melbourne International Airport , 1 Air Terminal Pkwy , Melbourne , FL 32901 , ☏ +1 321-723-6227 .
#Text=Serves Atlanta , Charlotte , and Washington DC at Dulles .
#Text=Palm Beach International Airport , 1000 Palm Beach International Airport , West Palm Beach , FL 33406 , ☏ +1 561-471-7400 .
#Text=Serving major airports from Boston to Dallas .
#Text=By train
#Text=There has been much talk and controversy about the Florida East Coast Railroad and Amtrak giving the Port St. Lucie area , possibly Fort Pierce , a train station that serves passengers .
#Text=If these plans go through , they will be serving the Florida East Coast Railway on rails that have not been touched by the rumbling wheels of passenger trains since the mid-1900s .
#Text=Also , there has been controversy of a high-speed rail project from Miami to Orlando with a station in West Palm Beach ; a station may be placed in the PSL area as well to accommodate .
#Text=The full plan is rebuilding a passenger line to re-connect the Treasure Coast and the Space Coast with the rest of the country , serving from Martin County to northern Brevard County .
#Text=The closest stations to date are in Okeechobee and West Palm Beach .
#Text=West Palm Beach , 209 South Tamarind Avenue
#Text=West Palm Beach , FL 33401 .
#Text=Ticket office , waiting room , and two different routes going two ways !
#Text=Okeechobee , 801 North Parrott Avenue
#Text=Okeechobee , FL 34972 .
#Text=Platform station with shelter .
#Text=Only a stopping location , no ticket office yet .
#Text=By bus
#Text=Greyhound Lines , ( bus station ) 7150 Okeechobee Rd ( Kings Highway and Okeechobee Road , north of the I-95/Florida Turnpike junction . ) , ☏ +1775 461-3299 , toll-free : +1 800 231-2222 .
#Text=M - Sa 7:30AM to 6:30PM and Su 7:30AM to 3:15PM .
#Text=They also have additional stops at a Shell Station on 1795 SW St Lucie West Rd in Port St Lucie and at a Sunoco Gas Station on 8418 20th St in Vero Beach .
#Text=The gas stations stops do NOT sell tickets .
#Text=Jet Set Express , ( bus stop )
#Text=Port St. Lucie-Fort Pierce Service Plaza ( MM 144 of the Florida Turnpike ) , ☏ +1407 649-4994 .
#Text=Venue at stop open 24/7 .

#Text=Port St. Lucie-Fort Pierce Service Plaza ( MM 144 of the Florida Turnpike , north of Crosstown Pkwy Jct ) , ☏ +1321 604-7188 , toll-free : +1 877-733-0724 .
#Text=Venue at stop open 24/7 .
